31
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:06,800
<i>[Memory of Encaustic Tile]</i>

32
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,600
<i>[Adapted from Beifeng Sanbaili's original novel "Memory of Encaustic Tile"]</i>

33
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:13,000
<i>[Episode 26]
[First Love is Not a Small Thing]</i>

34
00:02:18,599 --> 00:02:19,478
<i>You're early.</i>

35
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,800
<i>You're here.</i>

36
00:02:21,479 --> 00:02:22,079
<i>- You're here.
- You're early.</i>

37
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,900
Up there.

38
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:26,200
That's right. Go further up.

39
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,600
No rush. One at a time.

40
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:31,100
Okay.

41
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:33,800
Mr. Luo.

42
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,800
You're here.

43
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,000
All right. That's all for now.

44
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,400
Look.

45
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,800
From now on,

46
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:51,400
stop calling me Mr. Luo.

47
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,400
Call me, "Master."

48
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:58,000
I'll take you as my apprentice.

49
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,700
That doesn't seem appropriate.

50
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,200
There's nothing wrong with that.

51
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:03,200
I have the final say.

52
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:06,000
I'll talk to your dad later on.

53
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,400
Master.

54
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:20,800
Consider this a gift from your master.

55
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,000
Thank you, Master.

56
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,800
Put your work aside.

57
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,100
I have something to say.

58
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,900
I hereby make an official announcement

59
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,500
that I have a new apprentice now.

60
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,000
It's this handsome guy over here.

61
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:38,700
- Congratulations, Mr. Luo.
- Congratulations, Mr. Luo.

62
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,600
Say a few words.

63
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,800
Hi, I'm Zheng Sunian.

64
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:46,400
Nice to meet you.

65
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,500
- Be kind to him.
- Okay.

66
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,400
Welcome.

67
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,500
All right. Get back to work.

68
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:56,300
Look. This is your desk.

69
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:58,200
You have to come

70
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,600
20 minutes early for work every day

71
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,000
to sweep the floor and clean up the place.

72
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,400
Draw when you have time.

73
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:06,400
Once your drawing is up to standard,

74
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,900
you can start working on vintage items.

75
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:11,200
Remember. I'll evaluate and rate each of your drawings.

76
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,600
Got it.

77
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:15,500
Okay, now go get a pot of hot water.

78
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:40,000
<i>[Russian delegation, Recruiting translator]</i>

79
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,700
<i>[Looking to Olympic Games]</i>
The banner to the right.

80
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,900
Further up.

81
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:45,900
That's it.

82
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:47,900
Hello, Sunian.

83
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:50,100
Have you reached the Restoration Department?

84
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,400
I just fetched water.

85
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,600
How does it feel?

86
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,800
It's amazing, isn't it?

87
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,400
That's right.

88
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,200
Mr. Luo is now my master,

89
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,800
and my dad is my colleague.

90
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,800
You have ranked up.

91
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,800
I should call you Mr. Sunian now.

92
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,100
Sure.

93
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,600
Try me.

94
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,700
<i>You wish.</i>

95
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,200
Oh right, Sunian.

96
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,500
Come with me to the mall tonight.

97
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,600
I applied to take part in an English speech contest.

98
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,800
It's really important.

99
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,100
<i>I want to buy a formal dress.</i>

100
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:23,000
Sure, I'll buy it for you.

101
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,200
No, I have money.

102
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,800
Why don't you treat me to some good food?

103
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:30,000
Figure out what you want to have then.

104
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Well, let me think about it.

105
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,300
I'll let you know when I see you tonight.

106
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,800
See you tonight.

107
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,200
<i>See you.</i>

108
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,500
Xue!

109
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:46,600
Senior.

110
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,100
How is your speech preparation going?

111
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:49,800
Do you have the confidence to get first place?

112
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,800
Well, I'm well-prepared.

113
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:54,300
But I dare not imagine getting first place.

114
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:56,100
- Keep it up!
- Keep it up!

115
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,800
- Bye!
- Bye! I'll get going now!

116
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,600
Hello, Mom?

117
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,200
<i>Xue, listen carefully.</i>

118
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,900
<i>I want to divorce your dad.</i>

119
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,600
<i>Divorce!</i>

120
00:06:16,199 --> 00:06:17,999
Sunian is here, right?

121
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,600
Yes.

122
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:23,200
Quick question for you.

123
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,200
Your son is now your colleague.

124
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:27,200
How does that feel?

125
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,300
Shao Hua.

126
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,300
Shao Hua, my co-worker.

127
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:38,600
Who told you to take the breakfast from my table?

128
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:41,300
There are two portions.

129
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,900
I wanted to have one and take one to work.

130
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:46,400
We're not living together soon.

131
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,800
Start treating yourself as an outsider.

132
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,100
Don't touch my things.

133
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,000
Knock it off, will you?

134
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,200
Stop acting crazy.

135
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:01,200
Hey, what's going on?

136
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,400
You saw it, didn't you?

137
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,400
Your son is now your colleague.

138
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:12,000
My wife is now my co-worker.

139
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,200
What did I do to deserve this?

140
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,200
Just go over and cheer her up.

141
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,600
What for?

142
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,300
I did nothing wrong.

143
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:23,700
I won't let her have it her way!

144
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,300
What happened this time?

145
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,400
It's such a big house.

146
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,400
It's filled with her stuff.

147
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,300
I have only two small drawers.

148
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:35,800
Even that, she tried to find fault with me.

149
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,800
You can't imagine how messy his drawers are.

150
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,600
It's a pain in the neck.

151
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,000
I only meant well

152
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,700
and helped to clean it up for him.

153
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,600
But he said his stuff had gone missing.

154
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:48,100
He came yelling at me and gave me attitude.

155
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,800
I was through with things.

156
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,300
How much is his junk worth? So what if they go missing?

157
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:55,800
She lost my things and said I was collecting junk.

158
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:57,800
He said I was a junk collector.

159
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,900
It's not like he doesn't know that I love collecting fabrics?

160
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,900
Some clothes are old,

161
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:04,800
but the material is still good.

162
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,900
So I took them apart, sterilized them,

163
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,100
and sewed them up.

164
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:10,000
Isn't that another set of brand-new clothes?

165
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,200
What's wrong with that?

166
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,700
Even if I take those parts

167
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:14,600
and put them all over the table,

168
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,400
it won't be laden with them.

169
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,000
She gets two large wardrobes for herself.

170
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,600
Can't I have two small drawers?

171
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:25,100
But your drawers aren't small.

172
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:26,200
Whose side are you on?

173
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,800
I...

174
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,800
If this happened to you, you'd be mad too.

175
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,000
Those things in the drawers were all my precious babies.

176
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,200
I braved the wind and snow and got them

177
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:38,000
one by one from the flea market over the years.

178
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,700
Many of them were vintage items.

179
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:43,600
Look what she's done. Out of rage, she slammed my drawers

180
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,800
and threw everything on the floor.

181
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,600
Those small parts fell all over the place.

182
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,300
How am I to find them?

183
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,700
That's too much. Those parts are innocent.

184
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:53,300
- Right?
-That's right.

185
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,800
I didn't mean it.

186
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,000
Do you know how heavy his drawer is?

187
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,300
It's filled with junk.

188
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:00,600
It slipped out of my hand and fell on the floor.

189
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,800
I felt bad at that time.

190
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,200
I wanted to apologize to him.

191
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,800
But he came arguing with me.

192
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:09,000
He dug out all the fabrics and threw them on the floor.

193
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,300
He wanted to cut them with scissors.

194
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,200
So I said, "Try cutting them."

195
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:15,200
Well, did you cut them or did you not?

196
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,000
Of course...

197
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,200
"If you cut them, I'll fight you till the end!"

198
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,800
I dare not cut them.

199
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,200
She's a tigress, perfectly in one piece.

200
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,400
I'm no Wu Song.
<i>(A tiger-fighting hero in the novel "Water Margin")</i>

201
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,100
I wouldn't dare to mess with her.

202
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:33,300
So, in the end, you put them back?

203
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,400
I can't look bad though.

204
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,800
What I did was... Pah!

205
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,600
I threw them on the floor.

206
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,300
That, and she got mad again.

207
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:44,800
She started coming at me and scratched me with her claws.

208
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,200
Then?

209
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,200
So we fought.

210
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:52,400
Look! We've lived together for over a decade.

211
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,400
You can't imagine this.

212
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:56,000
He said things that were so nasty.

213
00:09:56,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Look. If you want to know how a man feels about you,

214
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,900
watch how he is when he fights with you.

215
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,300
You won't know if you don't fight.

216
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:06,200
But once you do, you can see him for who he really is.

217
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,800
He held it in all this time.

218
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,400
Do you know what he said about me?

219
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,600
Take a guess.

220
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,500
He called me a tigress

221
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,000
and said that I'm uncultured

222
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,300
and that I took away his human rights.

223
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:18,000
Don't laugh. He even called me the Queen of Junk.

224
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,000
So I had enough.

225
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,200
"I'm a junk collector." "Don't be with me then!"

226
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:24,900
- "Let's get a divorce!"
- Fine!

227
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,000
Who's afraid of her?

228
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,600
I'm sick of this trick.

229
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,200
She wanted to break up with me when we were young.

230
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,700
Now that we're older, she is asking for a divorce.

231
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,700
So be it.

232
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:37,000
It's not like we can't live without each other.

233
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,200
Yes, get a divorce.

234
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:41,300
I know someone in the Civil Affairs Bureau.

235
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,800
Putting a rush, are you?

236
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,400
Divorce?

237
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,700
Our girl is so big now.

238
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,700
<i>Hello!</i>

239
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:12,800
My daddy! Mommy!

240
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:14,000
Why are you back?

241
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,300
Well, I miss you guys.

242
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:19,600
Your mom must have given you a scare.

243
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,100
Where's Mom?

244
00:11:21,100 --> 00:11:22,800
She went visiting as soon as she got off work.

245
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:25,700
She said the sight of me made her feel irritated.

246
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,400
It's more serious than I thought.

247
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:31,800
I bet she's going through menopause.

248
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,800
I thought the same.

249
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,700
Well, Mr. Shao.

250
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,400
Since she's going through menopause,

251
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:41,000
you need to be steady.

252
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,800
Why pick fights with her?

253
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,800
There's no point even if I back down now.

254
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:48,300
She alone can pick fights for two.

255
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,400
You should know how Ms. Yu is.

256
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:53,000
She can get angry, but she won't cool herself off.

257
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,900
You need to cheer her up.

258
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:58,800
What about my anger?

259
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,400
Her pile of junk takes up two large wardrobes.

260
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,800
Why don't I have any right to have two small drawers?

